result.execSummary:
The defendant Chad Neal Lampson, #640924 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Credit for time served of 412 days.  Remanded to custody of Bayfield County Sheriff's Dept. for transport.  The court is unsure if eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  DOC to make final determination if eligible.

Amended 3-10-2016:  Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.

superMiscConds.notes: Court costs totaling $105.00.    If probation/extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant on behalf of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant is to undergo any counseling as recommended by Agent.  Complete a psycho-sexual evaluation and folow through with any recommendations by the provider.    Cognitive Behavior Class as directed by DOC agent.

No contact with the minor child, M.L., her residence or any area occupied by her; this includes third-party contact, contact in writing, by telephone, electronic or any digital means.  No contact with the minor child's immediate family or any person residing in any residence or place in which the minor child, M.L., so resides.  No unsupervised contact with any person under the age of 18 without prior agent approval.    As a convicted felon, prohibited from voting until civil rights restored.

Register as a sex offender for the rest of his natural life.  Comply with any and all supervision rules and counseling deemed appropriate by DOC, including sex offender rules and policies.    Defendant is to submit DNA sample.
As a convicted felon, prohibited from possessing a firearm.
